FOUR! Smashes this one! Faheem Ashraf drops it short again, around middle. Marnus Labuschagne picks up the length and pulls it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shows the full face of the bat and blocks it out solidly.
Another length ball, around the fifth stump line. Marnus Labuschagne walks across and blocks it out.
Fullish this time, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and defends it out.
Shortish ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja stays back and cuts it towards point for a single.

Slower through the air now, outside off, fuller ball. Marnus Labuschagne leans and looks to defend this but the ball goes off the outside edge past the first slip fielder towards third man. The batters take three runs!
Much fuller, around off. Usman Khawaja defends it out.
Short and on middle, Usman Khawaja rocks back and guides it to deep point. He crosses ends.
Full and on the pads, Marnus Labuschagne defends it.
Flatter ball, Marnus Labuschagne punches it towards covers.
Angling in, around middle, on a good length. Usman Khawaja defends it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at around 129 clicks. Usman Khawaja blocks it out.
Swinging in, outside off, on a length again. Usman Khawaja opens the face of the bat and dabs it towards point for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne taps it towards point and rotates the strike!
Length, outside off. Usman Khawaja miscues his drive towards cover.
FOUR! Top shot! Faheem Ashraf drops it short now, angling in on middle. Usman Khawaja swivels and pulls it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Perfectly executed! A fuller delivery, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets down on his knee and reverse-sweeps it past point for a boundary.
Fuller again, around off. Marnus Labuschagne leans and defends this one.
FOUR! Another boundary! Lovely shot once again! Outside off, fuller delivery. Marnus Labuschagne leans and drives it past cover for a beautiful boundary!
Fuller again, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes it towards cover for a  single.
Tosses it up now, full again, around middle. Usman Khawaja defends this one.
Outside off, fuller ball. Usman Khawaja leans to defend this but he misses and the ball hit shim on the pads. Half an appeal for LBW, but the umpire is unmoved!
Fuller now, around middle and leg. Marnus Labuschagne flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja leaves it alone.
On a length, shaping away, wide of off. Usman Khawaja offers no shot once again.
Very full this time, outside off. Usman Khawaja squeezes it out towards point for a single.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it towards cover-point for single.
Another length delivery, outside off. Usman Khawaja defends it towards cover.

FOUR! The Aussies further stamping that Pakistan's 148 isn't a real reflection of the pitch. Full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets low and sweeps it to the vacant deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Full again, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne walks across and blocks it out.
Outside off, worked to square leg for a single.

DROPPED! Tosses it up, around off, stays a bit little low. Usman Khawaja looks to defend it off the back foot but gets a little tickle. Mohammad Rizwan however fails to pouch it. A similar kind of delivery to which he got out in the first innings.
Flighted delivery, on middle and leg. Usman Khawaja prods and keeps it out.
Tosses it up, outside off. Usman Khawaja pushes it to the off side for a run.
Floats it up, on off. Usman Khawaja flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Angling in with the arm, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne puts a big stride forward and blocks.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked.
Loopy ball, on off. Defended to short leg.
Full and on off, pushed towards covers.

SIX! Pakistan players are hurt and this batting from Australia is adding more fuel to the fire. Tossed up delivery, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne gets to the pitch of the ball and smacks it over long off. Didn't hit it off the middle but still has enough legs to clear the ropes. A maximum!
Flatter, on middle. Blocked out to the leg side off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Usman Khawaja is solid in his defence.
Full and on middle and leg, Usman Khawaja plays a paddle sweep. The ball rolls to fine leg for a brace.
Slower ball, on middle. Usman Khawaja keeps it out.
Flatter delivery, on the pads. Defended.
Full and on middle, Usman Khawaja strides forward and looks to defend. The ball goes off the inner half and past short leg for a single. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
On the fuller side to begin with, outside off, Khawaja strokes it to covers.
Errs down the leg side, Khawaja looks to flick but misses.
Over compensates now and bowls this one well wide outside off. Easy leave.

EDGY FOUR! First runs for today! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Khawaja looks to defend, he tries to do so away from the body. It goes off the outside edge down to third man for a boundary.
Good length and on off, this one stays a touch low. Khawaja defends towards cover for one.
Two more to end a good first over for the Aussies. Shorter and outside off, this is guided through point. The man in the deep runs to his left, dives and keeps it down to two.
Length ball, angling in, on middle and leg. Usman Khawaja clips it to square leg for a single.
Edged but didn't carry! Length ball, moving away, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne has a poke. The ball kisses the outside edge but dies on the way through. Falls well short of Mohammad Rizwan.
Back of a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne Marnus Labuschagne steers it through cover-point for a couple.
On a length, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne dabs it to third man for one.
Back of a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja works it one-handed on the leg side for a single.
Jaffa! Good length, outside off, angling away at 143 clicks. Marnus Labuschagne tries to defend but the ball whistles past the outside edge.
Fuller, on off. Usman Khawaja defends it out towards covers.
Sliding leg side, Usman Khawaja tickles it. Mohammad Rizwan does well o dive to his right and stop the ball. Saved a certain boundary there!
Back of a length, on middle, Usman Khawaja gets behind the line and knocks it back to the bowler.
Touch fuller, on off. Usman Khawaja prods and blocks it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja taps it behind point and crosses ends.
An inswinging ball, on a length, Marnus Labuschagne keeps it out.
On length and outside off, Khawaja tries to steer it to third man but couldn't beat Fawad Alam at gully.
Full and on middle and leg, defended to mid on.
Length, outside off, Usman Khawaja dabs it down to deep point for a run.
On a length, on middle. Marnus Labuschagne tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Length ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja lifts his bat and lets it go.
That kept low! Length ball, around off. Usman Khawaja blocks it off the bottom half of the bat.
Outside off, Marnus Labuschagne steers it to deep point for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Usman Khawaja lets it sail through.
Short of a length, outside off, again keeping a fraction low. Usman Khawaja covers the line and blocks.
Full and quick, on middle and leg. Usman Khawaja nudges it on the leg side.
Full, on leg. Blocked out.
On a length, outside off. Usman Khawaja keeps it out. A good over by Hasan Ali.
Length ball, outside off, Marnus Labuschagne offers no shot.
Length ball, shaping away, outside off. Marnus Labuschagne goes for the drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! TIMBER! Shaheen Afridi gets the breakthrough. He is delighted and pumped up. Some celebration for Pakistan! Back of a length, outside off, once again it keeps a little low. Marnus Labuschagne looks to work it on the leg side. The ball goes off the inside edge and ricochets back onto the stumps. He departs for 44 and with that, Australia says the runs are enough. No new batter comes out to bat and Australia have declared at 97/2. They have a mammoth lead of 505 runs.
Howout: b Shaheen Afridi

Commentary: Mitchell Starc starts with an inswinging ball, on a fuller length. Abdullah Shafique clips it on the leg side with the inner half of the bat.
A full toss, outside off, Abdullah Shafique watches the ball and lets it be.
Touch fuller, outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to drive but gets beaten.
Full and on leg, nudged to mid on.
Full and wide, outside off, Abdullah Shafique steps forward and shoulders arms.
Beauty! Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Abdullah Shafique goes for a drive again but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and on off, Imam-ul-Haq drives it back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. Imam-ul-Haq knocks it to the off side.
Angling away from a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq looks to defend but the ball beats the outside edge.
Length, on off. Imam-ul-Haq pats it towards point and calls for a single but is sent back. Pakistan would not want another run out here.
Good-length ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq prods and pushes it towards covers.

Two maidens in a row for Australia! Pakistan yet to get underway! Another peach from Pat Cummins. Good length, shaping away, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq tries to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms.
Length and wide again, outside off. Abdullah Shafique lets it be.
Starc goes full and quick, outside off. Abdullah Shafique continues his leaving spree.
Full again, outside off. This time Abdullah Shafique drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Back of a length now, on off. Abdullah Shafique hops and blocks it to the off side.
Another maiden! Fuller in length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique drives it firmly to mid off.
Length and outside off, left alone.
Nicely bowled! Slightly shorter and angling away from off. Imam drops his hands and lets it go.
Slightly fuller and on off, Imam pushes it to mid off. Excellent from Australia, giving nothing away and keeping the pressure going.
That is sharp! Short and on middle, Imam does well to evade it. That was a real effort ball from Cummins.

Not sure why Imam is so keen for a run, the two were involved in a run out in the first innings and here too Imam just wants to run for everything. On a length and around off, he pushes it back towards the bowler. It hits the stumps at the other end and goes on the off side. Imam wants one but is sent back.
Good length and on off, Imam defends.
Flatter and on middle, Abdullah Shafique stays back and blocks.
Pakistan are underway and so is Abdullah Shafique! On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Imam gets off the mark too! Shorter and outside off, Imam stays back, a little bit of extra bounce. He guides it through point for one.
Tossed up on middle, defended.

Turn and bounce! Beautifully bowled. This lands on off, it draws Abdullah Shafique forward to defend, it pitches, takes off and then spins away sharply. Abdullah Shafique is beaten as he tries to block. Now this is what will happen, this is probably going to get tougher as the game goes on.
The googly probably to end. On middle, Abdullah Shafique blocks.
Flatter and on middle, Imam hangs back and defends.
This one stays low! On middle, this does not bounce a lot. Imam does well to get his bat down in time and work it on the leg side.
Solid! Flatter and on middle, Imam lunges and keeps it out.
Fires it on middle, Imam goes back and blocks.

OUT! THREE REDS! Australia have their first! That is as plumb as it gets. A waste of a review. This is flatter and on middle, Imam looks to defend by coming forward but does so for the turn. This one goes on with the angle and hits him on the front pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Imam reviews after a chat with his partner but to no avail. Early strike, just what the Aussies wanted.
Howout: lbw b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Flatter and on middle, defended. End of a successful first over by Lyon.
Flatter and on middle, Abdullah Shafique blocks.
A full toss, this is worked wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Shorter and on off, Abdullah Shafique stays back and pushes it through covers for one.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it outside off, Azhar pushes it to covers.
On middle, defended well.
On middle, defended.
On middle, defended.
Quicker and on middle, Abdullah Shafique hangs back and blocks it.
Two more! On middle, Abdullah Shafique works it down to fine leg for two.
Loopy ball and on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to covers.
On middle, it is defended well.
Another one quicker and on off. Blocked.
Fuller and on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Floats it up on off, Ali pushes it to mid off.
Good leave in the end! Outside off, This one holds its line. Ali makes a good leave.
On the stumps, Ali is solid in defense again.
That seems to be the slider, it is on middle, stays a touch low. Ali does well to hang back and keep it out.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Another one tossed up and on off, defended.
Gives it aur and lands it on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and blocks.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique works it to mid-wicket.
Another one on middle, Abdullah Shafique plays it onto the ground.
Yet again on the stumps, Abdullah Shafique manages to play it back to the bowler. Solid from the batter and excellent stuff from the bowler too.
Magical stuff! Slower through the air, it lands on off and then spins away. Ali lunges and tries to defend but this one spins away sharply. Ali is beaten.
Angled into the pads, Azhar works it to square leg.
On the stumps, defended.
Shorter and on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
Loopy ball on off, Ali blocks.
Shorter and on off, Azhar pushes it through covers for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.
Floats it up on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
On middle, defended.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to mid off.
Solid yet again! Floats it up on off, Ali shows the full face of the bat and defends.
Another maiden! Lyon has 3 in 4 ovrs. On the stumps, it is pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it back to the bowler.
Really good stuff from Mitchell Swepson! He has been landing it so well. Again, tosses it up nicely and lands it on off, it is played out.
A little too full this time and on the pads, it is worked through square leg for two.
Fuller and on middle, Abdullah Shafique pushes it uppishly but it lands well short of the bowler.
On the stumps, kept out.
Another one tossed up and on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to covers.
Flatter and on middle, Azhar Ali hangs back and keeps it out.
On middle, Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball and on middle, kept out.
Quicker and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Ali plays it back to the bowler.
Floats it up, lands it on off, Ali plays it out.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks.
Full and on middle, squeezed out.
Flatter, on middle. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Full and on middle, defended to short leg.
Quicker, outside off. Pushed to the off side.
Full again, on off. Driven to mid off.
Outside off, Ali is solid in his defence.
Loopy, on off. Ali blocks it out.
On middle, played to mid-wicket.
Very full, on off. Ali eases it to long on for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique lunges forward and blocks.
Full and on off, kept out.
Flatter, on middle. Ali clears his front leg and pushes it to mid off.
Loopy, on off. Ali blocks it out.
Azhar Ali with a solid forward press.
Short and outside off, cut away to sweeper cover for a single.
On the pads, nudged to square leg for a run.
On off, defended.
Loopy ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it from the crease.
Floats it up, outside off. Knocked in front of long on for a run.
Extra bounce, on leg. Azhar Ali defends it to short leg.
Slower through the air, on middle. Ali blocks it out.
Loopy ball, keeps low, on middle. Ali does well to bring his bat down in time.
Flatter, on middle. Ali stays solid in his defence.
On a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Good length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms.
Length, on off. Defended to mid off.
Just a hint of away movement on this length delivery, played to point for a single.
Good-length ball, on middle. Ali stands tall and blocks.
Bit of inward shape on this full delivery, Azhar Ali defends towards point.
Full and on the pads, worked away to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller length, outside off, steered to backward point for a single.
Short ball, on off. Azhar Ali hops and defends.
Full and on off, defended from the crease.
Full and wide of off, Azhar Ali lets it go.
Full and quick on off, angling into the batter, defended back to the bowler.
Length delivery on off, Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Length delivery on the fourth stump, Abdullah Shafique defends it off the front foot.
Fuller in length this time just outside off, defended on the off side.
Short ball on middle, Shafique ducks under it.
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique mistimes his drive towards covers.
Fuller in length, Shafique defends it back to the bowler from the crease. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Well bowled! Mitchell Swepson once again starts off well. Flatter, it lands on middle, spins away a touch. Ali defends it late.
Another one tossed up and on off, Ali blocks it out.
Attacks the stumps again and it is flatter. Ali plays it back to the bowler.
Pushes it through but bowls it outside off, left alone.
First run of the session! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Angled into the pads, looking to turn it away. AS defends.
A little bit of movement for Green! On middle, it comes back in. This is worked through mid-wicket for one.

OUT! LBW! That is unplayable! Green himself can't believe he has a wicket that way. What a move to begin with Green as he strikes on just his second ball. He bangs it shorter in length. Ali looks to duck under it, this one just does not bounce at all. It hits Ali near the thigh pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Both the batters are having a discussion but time runs out. Perfect start for the Aussies. Ultra Edge shows a spike as it passed the glove. Not sure why the review was not taken there. Ali is such a big wicket, really not good from Pakistan, they wasted a review earlier on when it seemed dead out, this time, there were quite a few doubts but the review was not taken. Wondering how Ali did not realise he did not get glove on it, maybe he was just in shock of how low the ball kept there.
Howout: lbw b Cameron Green

Commentary: Good length and on off, defended.
Azam is off the mark! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Fraction short around middle and leg, Shafique tucks it into the leg side for one.
Tosses it up, outside off. Blocked.
This is cut away to deep point for a run.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam defends it on the leg side.
Full and on off, played to mid on.
On off, kept out.
Floats it up, on off. Azam stays solid in his defence.
This one comes back in, Abdullah Shafique defends it well. Green is getting some nice movement.

Kept low again! The key here was Abdullah Shafique kept his eyes on the ball unlike Azhar Ali! This is shorter and on middle, Abdullah Shafique has to adjust as this one does not bounce a lot. He pulls it through square leg for one. Not sure if the pull shots are the right way to go on this wicket.
This one bounces nicely! This is very short, Azam ducks under it. This is not a bad ploy from Green to bang it short like this, one is keeping low and the other is bouncing nicely.
On middle, Azam strokes it back towards the bowler.
Shorter and on middle, Azam pulls it through square leg for one.
Another one outside off, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Azam works it down to long on and takes one.
Tossed up and on off, defended.
Well bowled again! Swepson has been really impressive! Gives it flight and lands it on off, it ptches and turns away. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it goes off the outer half on the off side.
Close again! This lands around leg, Abdullah Shafique looks to defend, it goes off the inside edge past short leg and towards square leg for one.
FOUR! Slapped away! First boundary of this innings! Azam won't be blocking everything, he will play his shots. Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for a boundary.
Takes one now! On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
Good length and on middle, Azam blocks it out.
Azam moves onto 9 in no time! Around off, Azam guides it through point for one.
Angles it into the pads, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Gets it to move the other way now, length and on off, it lands and moves away, it is guided through point for one.
Goes short, Azam watches it till the end and then ducks under it.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Azam drives it hard but to covers.
On the pads, Azam looks to flick, the ball turns away. It goes off the leading edge but a soft one towards mid off.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
On middle, defended.
Flatter and on middle, Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Good shot but only one! Outside off, shorter. Abdullah Shafique stays back and slaps it through covers for one.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Steven Smith is the culprit! Cummins almost struck on the very first ball. That should have been taken. This is maybe his second or third dropped catch. This one though was easy. Length and on off, it lands and moves away. Abdullah Shafique pokes at it, it goes off the outside edge. It gets to Smith quickly at first slip who is standing quite close. He fails to hang on. Can Abdullah Shafique make the most of this chance?
Good length and outside off, left alone.
Another one on a length, this time Shafique gets right behind the line and plays it to mid off.
Angled into middle, a little bit of swing into the batter. Abdullah Shafique works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid off.
Good leave! This is in the 5th stump channel. Abdullah Shafique watches it and lets it go through to the keeper.
From around the wicket, bowls a loosener first up! Down the leg side. Azam looks to flick but misses.
Fuller and on off, Azam shows the full face of the bat and plays it to mid off.

Azam has a poke there! He gets beaten! The around the wicket angle, that is the reason why he played at it. Starc from wide of the crease angles it in, it lands on a crack and then moves away. Azam plays at it away from the body but gets beaten.
Shot! Fuller and on off, Azam shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid off.
Good length and on off, Azam blocks.

Bowls a yorker now and on off, Azam gets his bat down in time. Not a lot of reverse for both Starc and Cummins. They are getting a little bit of it but nothing like what happened in the first innings.
That one stays low! Outside off, no bounce at all. Left alone.
Good length and on middle, Abdullah Shafique stays back and defends.
Solid again! On the stumps, it is defended. There is one odd ball which is staying low but otherwise, the wicket still seems a decent one to bat on especially with the ball not reversing.
On the stumps, kept out again.
On the middle stump, Abdullah Shafique plays it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Not sure if that is a shot Azam would have been happy with seeing from the other end! It is a length delivery outside off. Abdullah Shafique hangs his bat out, he ends up playing away from the body. It goes more off the outer half down to the third man fence. That could have easily taken the edge and gone to the keeper. Need to leave those.

EDGY FOUR! Length and on off, Azam stands tall and looks to defend, he looks to do so by playing it close to his body and also with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge wide of second slip and down to the third man fence. It is also a no ball.
He was almost tempted! Outside off, fuller. Azam thinks about going after it but then leaves it alone.
Good length and on middle, defended.
On middle, defended.
Fuller and on middle, Azam works it to mid on.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, Azam nudges it down to fine leg for one.

FOUR! Uppish but just wide! Babar would have been worried for a minute! Shorter and on middle, Azam pulls, he does not get on top of the bounce completely and hence, it goes in the air but wide of mid-wicket for a boundary.
Now takes one as he works it through square leg. This is the thing with Azam, he will look to score.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
FOUR! That has been cracked! Shorter in length and on off, fractionally short actually. Abdullah Shafique pulls it hard over square leg for a boundary.
Drop and run! Shorter and on off, Abdullah Shafique drops it towards point for one.
Fuller this time and tailing back in. First time in this innings we saw the ball come back in the way it did. Azam plays it to mid on.
Fuller and on middle, it is defended.
Abdullah Shafique is just in the mind set of blocking here. This is a full toss on off, he just puts bat to ball.
He is just not looking to hit it hard! Here too, it is a half volley outside off, Abdullah Shafique just puts bat on ball and guides it through point for one.
Two more! Outside off, Azam guides it through point for two.
Another run! Runs coming nicely for Pakistan now! Outside off, this is guided through point for one.
Close! Length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to leave it alone but tries to do so late. It hits the underedge and goes on the bounce to the keeper.
Good-length delivery tailing back in, Babar Azam defends from the crease.
Short ball, outside off. Babar Azam manages to get out of the way.
Length ball, nipping in, on off. Azam blocks it under his eyes.
Full and on middle, turned to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery just outside off stump, Babar defends off the back foot.
Short and into the body, Azam gets under that one and lets it go through to the keeper.
Floats it up, leg. Abdullah Shafique glances it to square leg.
Full and on the stumps, Shafique clips it past short leg for a single.
On the pads, Azam nudges it to square leg for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Kept out.
Some extra bounce! Loopy ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique works it behind square leg for a brace.
Floated outside off, Shafique defends it onto the pitch.
On a length, on the pads. Azam tickles it to fine leg for a single.
Full and shaping in late on the stumps, Shafique drives it along the ground to mid on.

Huge shout for an lbw but turned down! Length ball, sliding down leg, Abdullah Shafique misses his tuck and gets hit on the pads. Australia appeal but the umpire says no. The ball rolls on the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam keeps it out.
Short and that one was into the head, Azam somehow manages to get out of the way of that one. Good pacy and a well-directed bouncer!
Good length, on top of off. Azam knocks it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique plays it mid on for a quick single. A direct-hit would have been curtains for Shafique. He would have gifted his wicket for the second time in the game.
On off, blocked.
Full and on off, Azam presses forward and blocks.
Loopy, on middle, shapr turn there. Azam does well to block it out.
Flighted, outside off. Azam defends it on the leg side.
Floated outside off, Azam prods forward and taps it towards point region.
Tossed up on middle, Shafique defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball, on off. Shafique defends it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, on off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Full and on the stumps, Shafique tucks it to short leg.
Very full delivery, Shafique defends.
On off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it to silly point.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short and outside off, Babar Azam hangs back and cuts it towads deep point for a boundary. He loves to play that shot.
Now Babar Azam takes a single by working it to long on.
Tossed up outside off, Shafique presses forward and blocks it.
Floats it up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Flighted ball, on off, Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Defended.
Tosses it up, on off. Defended.
Full and quicker, on off. Azam jams it out.
Full again, on off. Azam is solid in his defence.
FOUR! A low full toss, on off. Babar Azam gets down on one knee and paddles it to fine leg for a boundary.
Outside off, turning away. Azam blocks it off the back foot. Mitchell Swepson targetting the cracks there.
Azam with a solid defence.
Floated outside off, Shafique prods and blocks it.
SIX! Abdullah Shafique takes the aerial route! Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique shimmies down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball. Hammers it over long on for a bigige. He moves to 40!
On the pads, defended.
Full and on middle, Abdullah Shafique covers the line and keeps it out.
On middle, blocked.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends.
Full and sliding down leg, Babar Azam tickles it to fine leg for a brace.
Full and on middle, blocked.
FOUR BYES! Way down the leg side, stays low as well. Babar Azam misses his sweep. Alex Carey tries to stop it with his legs but could not do so. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Full and on middle, Babar Azam drives but hits it to the silly point fielder.
FOUR! Another boundary! Short and on middle, Babar Azam makes room and punches that away through the covers and the ball races away to the fence.
Full and down the leg again, Azam misses his tuck and the keeper manages to glove it towards short fine leg this time.
The ball hits the crack and moves away. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it goes past his outside edge by quite some distance.
Full, on off. Driven back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Shafique offers no shot to that one.
Full and on off, Shafique presses forward and defends it towards extra cover.
Full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Very full outside off, Shafique defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, driven towards covers.
Floated ball, on leg, Azam flicks that away towards square leg and gets two.
Full and on middle, played to mid on.
Tossed up, on off. Azam defends it towards covers.
Full and on off, nudged to mid on.
Very full and on the leg stump, Babar drives it towards mid on.
A yorker, on off, angling in. Abdullah Shafique digs it out.
Full and outside off, Shafique defends it towards mid off.
Full and on leg, Shafique turns it towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! Starc errs in his line and bowls it down leg, Abdullah Shafique tickles it to fine leg. Alex Carey dives to his left but could not get his hands on it. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.
Very full, outside off. Kept out to the off side.
Full and on middle, Shafique plays a good defensive shot.
Full and angling down leg, that one keeps low as well as. Babar Azam misses his flick. It goes through to the keeper.
On a length, on off. Azam blocks it out.
Fuller, on off. Azam defends.

FOUR! Put away! Short ball, outside off. Babar Azam stands tall and pulls it over mid-wicket. Just over the fielder and the ball races away to the fence. The hosts have done a brilliant job with this partnership to deny Australia any more wickets after the Azhar Ali break!
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on middle, defended to mid on.
Full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique lets it sail through.
Back of a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it from the crease.
A wide yorker, outside off. The ball shoots up after hitting the footmark. Abdullah Shafique leaave it alone. Alex Carey does well to collect it moving to his right.
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique with a solid front foot defence.
Short and angling down leg, Shafique ducks under that one.
Short of a length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it to the off side. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Short ball, on off. Babar Azam pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique turns it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique stands tall and defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, the ball stays low. Abdullah Shafique sways away and lets it go.
Length ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique dabs it to deep backward point for one.
Short, outside off. Azam decides to leave it untouched.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Easily worked down the ground to long on for a run.
Tosses it up, wide outside off. Babar Azam leans and crunches his drive to wide of deep cover for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Kept out.
Outside off, the ball keeps a little low. Abdullah Shafique works it to mid on for one.

FIFTY! Floats it up, outside off. Babar Azam rocks back and pushes it to the off side for a single. Played a lone battle in the first innings and is playing a fine knock in the second innings as well. His 20th Test fifty! Abdullah Shafique comes up to him to congratulate. The crowd erupts as well to give him a huge cheer.
Floated around middle and leg, Shafique pushes it to mid on for one.
Angled into middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
An inswinger, coming in from around middle, Azam plays it right under his eyes.
Another one on middle, kept out well.
Probably misreads the length. This is a lot fuller and on off, Azam is rooted to his crease as he blocks.
Solid again! On middle, this is played to mid on.
A harmless nut to end! Down the leg side. Azam looks to flick but misses.
That almost sneaks through. Shafique comes down the track. He does not get to the pitch of it but does well to play it with the spin through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on off, pushed to cover.
Tossed up on off, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked on the leg side for one.
Flatter and on middle, Shafique works it to short leg.
Another over goes by! On middle, AS leans forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length and on off, this is kept out.
Relentless stuff from Green but solid from Azam! On off, Azam gets right behind the line and defends.
Good length and on off, Azam plays it to cover.

Well played in the end! Shorter and on middle, Azam was unsure whether to move out of the way or play it. He tries to move out in the end but too late by then. He does well though to guide it toward point for one.
Almost! Length and on off, tails back in. Shafique looks to defend but does so away from the body. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
This time he plays this one close to his body and back to the bowler.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled all along the ground through square leg for one.
Fifty for Shafique! A stubborn knock from him and a crucial one. He can't throw it away now. Needs to go on. He gets there with a deft touch. Guides this one outside off down to third man for three.
Floated up on off, blocked.
Another one tossed up on off, Azam keeps it out.
Gives it air and lands it on off, Azam comes forward and plays it to covers.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flighted ball to end, Shafique plays it back to where it comes from.
Starts off with a loosener well wide outside off. Left alone.
Very well bowled but well played too. A yorker from around the wicket on off, it is jammed out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Goes fuller, no movement at all for Starc. Blocked.
Angled into middle, defended.
Maiden by Starc. Another over goes by! Back of a length and on middle, blocked.
Short and outside off, Abdullah Shafique steers it to deep point for a single.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Outside off, pushed to sweeper cover for one. 100-run stand comes up between these two!
Full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique lunges and blocks.
Full and on off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Defended.
On a length, on middle. Azam turns it to mid-wicket.
Full and angling down leg, Babar Azam misses his flick.
Back of a length, on middle. Babar Azam stands tall, gets behind the line and blocks it with a dead bat.
Short of a length, down the leg side. Babar Azam misses his glance. Almost nicks it behind to Carey.
On a length, on off. Kept out.
FOUR! That's a beautiful shot! Fuller in length, outside off. Babar Azam opens the face of the bat and steers it to deep point for a glorious boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and the ball goes off the outside edge to the off side.
Full and on middle, blocked.
Full again, on leg. Kept out.
Loopy ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique hangs back and defends.
On off, blocked out.
A maiden! Full and on middle. Abdullah Shafique stays solid in his defence.
Full and outside off, pushed through cover-point for a single.
On a length, on middle. Abdullah Shafique offers a straight bat.
Length ball, outside off, Abdullah Shafique lets it sail through.
Short of a length, angling in, outside off. Abdullah Shafique does well to sway away from that line.
Short of a length, on off. Abdullah Shafique rides the bounce and steers this through backward point for a single.
That's a peach by Starc! Goes full outside off and the ball seams away. Babar Azam has a poke but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter, on off. Abdullah Shafique pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to the off side.
On the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips it to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven uppishly towards covers for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Babar Azam carves this to the man at point.
FOUR! Sprayed down the leg side, Babar Azam gets a faint tickle as he attempts a flick. Beats the keeper and gets a boundary as the ball races away to fine leg.
Good length and on off, this is guided towards point for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
That one does not rise a lot! Shorter and on middle. Azam watches it till the end and blocks.

EDGY FOUR! Starc will be happy about the fact that he made Azam play away from the body. Not the result he wanted though. Fuller and outside off, Azam goes after it, it goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence. Frustration grows for the Aussies.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Yet another one on a length and on off, this is played towards cover for one. Azam is playing it nice and late, right under his eyes.

That is loose from Azam. Not something you want to play when the ball is turning and when you're trying to save a game. This is tossed up, outside off, not full enough for a drive. Azam flashes at it but is beaten.
On middle, blocked.
Floats it up on middle, blocked again.
Close! Swepson seems quite close to getting a wicket. Shorter and this stays low. Azam pulls, it goes off the bottom towers mid-wicket for one.
Well folded! Shorter and outside off, Shafique cuts. But Starc at point dives to his right and stops.
The slider to end on middle, kept out well. A good over by Swepson.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
Tossed up on off, blocked.

Overthrows! More runs! Outside off, turning back in. Azam guides it towards deep point. They take two. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. It goes down to long on where Khawaja midfields and a run is taken.
On middle, kept out.
Comes down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Kept out.
A single to end! On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Nice and fine! Runs flowing now! A full toss on the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for a boundary down to fine leg.
Sharp turn! This lands on off and spins away. Shafique looks to defend but it goes off the outer half but wide of second slip/
Well bowled again! On off, blocked.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and around off, this is guided to point.
Well played! On middle, kept out. End of another good over by Swepson.
This is where Lyon has to bowl more! Floated up on off, defended.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
Nice and fine! On middle, this is tucked away towards fine leg for two.
Flatter and on off, this is guided to point.
On middle, this is worked to long on for one.
That is the perfect spot! Flight ball on off, Shafique looks to defend. This turns back in and goes off the inner half on the leg side.
On middle, spinning away. Babar Azam hangs back and keeps it out. The ball rolls back on the way to disturb the stumps but Babar Azam kicks it away.
And again! Babar is playing with softest of hands that the ball is rolling back off his bat.
Full and outside off, kept out.
Mitchell Swepson comes 'round the wicket and pitches it into the footmarks down leg, Babar Azam tries to pad it away. The ball wasn't far from hitting the leg pole.
Azam flicks this loopy ball to mid-wicket.
On off, kept out.
On off, blocked out.
Full and on off, driven to long on for one.
On middle, defended.
Very full, driven on the leg side.
Full and outside off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks.
Loopy ball, well outside off, Babar Azam plays the line and pads it away. Optimistic appeal for an LBW from the Aussies there!
A full toss, down leg. Abdullah Shafique tickles it to leg slip. The fielder there does well to stop the ball.
Full and on the pads, worked to square leg for a run.
Babar Azam pads it away as the ball pitches outside leg.
WIDE! Sprayed way down leg, Babar Azam leaves it alone. Wided.
Tossed up on leg stump line, Babar lunges forward to offer pad.
Flatter, down leg. Padded away again.
Outside leg, kicked away again.
Loopy ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique defends.
Flighted, full and on off, Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
Abdullah Shafique blocks this off the front foot.
This is driven to long on for a single.
Flatter, on middle and leg. Babar Azam works it to deep square leg for one.
On middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique blocks it out.
Full and pitching outside leg, Babar Azam misses his sweep and misses. Initially thought he's got something on it, but it's just missed everything to run down to third man. Given runs off bat though!
Full and outside leg, Babar Azam tries to pad it away but misses.
On the pads, worked to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted, full and on leg, Abdullah Shafique knocks it back to the bowler.

NO BALL! Full and pitching outside leg, Abdullah Shafique gets low and tries to sweep. The ball goes off the top edge and luckily, it goes onto hit the helmet. Could have easily been a catch to short leg if not for the helmet. Mandatory concussion check to follow. Replay shows that there was no bat at all. Just went straight off the rough to hit the helmet. Mitchell Swepson will have to reload as he has overstepped.
Full and on leg, kept out.
Outside off, blocked.
On middle, Azam works it to square leg.
On middle, Azam goes back and defends.
This time he gets it away of the fielder at backward square leg and takes one.
On middle, defended.
Floated up on off, kept out.
On the stumps, defended yet again.
On the pads, Azam kicks it away.
Very full, Azam sweeps it down to fine leg for one.
On the stumps, blocked.
WIDE! That turned big though. It lands well outside leg. In the rough and turns towards leg pole. AS looks to pad it away but misses. Not that close to the leg pole though. But turned big.
On middle, kept out.
Tires the surprise ball, lands it on off, googly, blocked.
Almsot sneaks through! On leg. Abdullah goes back and looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shorter and on middle, defended.
NO BALL SIGNALED FOR AN EXTRA FIELDER BEHIND SQUARE! Don't see this often! Shorter and on middle, defended.
FOUR! Put away! Shorter and outside off, this is played through point for a boundary.
Drop and run! There was a direct hit but the batter was well in. Shorter and on middle, this is pushed towards cover and one is taken.
Good length and on off, defended.
That stays low! Good thing is AS did not take his eyes off the ball. On middle, Shafique goes back and looks to fend. It hits the toe end.
From around the wicket now! Shafique stands tall and defends this bumper. This one bounces nicely.
Floats it up on leg. Kept out.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
The googly on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, defended.
This is swept through square leg for one.
A dot to end! Another over ends. 8 to go today. On middle, defended. Also, the 150 stand was on up on the last ball. The two just need to keep going.
Tap and run! On off, this is pushed to cover for one.
Shorter and around off, dabbed to backward point for one.
FOUR! Azam moves onto 94! Short and it comes slow off the surface. Azam pulls it through mid-wicket and bags a boundary.
Onto 95 now! On the body, this is nudges through square leg for one.
We'll bowled! This one comes back in from outside off. Stays low too. Defended.
Angled into the pads, this is clipped to mid-wicket.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Half an appeal but that is never going to be out! A full toss down the leg side. Shafique looks to push at it but it hits the boot and goes down to fine leg for one. Leg bye.
Outside leg. Babar pads it away.
On middle, defended.
On the pads, it is padded away again.
So close! This is fuller and down the leg side. Azam looks to sweep, it goes off the glove, close past the leg pole and down to fine leg for two.
Fires this one down leg, Abdullah Shafique misses his flick.
Fuller, on off. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks.
Abdullah Shafique works this towards point and gives the strike to Babar Azam.
Well bowled! Right into the blockhole, on off. Babar Azam squeezes it out.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam taps it to the off side. Big shout of no! No need to take unnecessary risks!
That one keeps low! Pat Cummins can't believe his luck. Good-length ball, on off. Babar Azam gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single. Babar Azam on 99!
Full and on middle, kept out.
Full and outside leg, Babar Azam defends it out.

TOP EDGE AND OVER WARNER AT SHORT FINE! Hundred for Azam. Cometh the hour cometh the man. Don’t remember the last time he scored a ton in a Test, he was due and has come off at the right time. A knock of high quality. His side needed someone to step up, they had their backs against the wall and it is then skipper who leads from the front. A wicket where the ball is staying low, turning, bouncing, he has played so fluently. A knock for the ages. He though needs to go on for longer, this is only half the job done. He plays a sweep to this ball down the leg side. It goes over short fine leg. Warner runs after it, dives and keeps it down to two. Takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause.
Outside leg, Babar Azam kicks it away.
Well down the leg side and turning in from the roughs, kicked away again.
On off, Babar Azam leans forward and defends.
On off, kept out.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
Outside off, Abdullah Shafique hangs back and defends.
Fuller, this is eased down to long on for one.
Shorter and outside off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On middle, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Quicker and on middle, kept out.
On the pads, worked to mid-wicket.
Fired down leg, Babar misses the glance, the ball hits the keeper's pad.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, Babar Azam prods and keeps it out.
Length ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique looks to work it on the leg side. The ball goes off the leading edge and rolls to backward point for a single.
How's that for swing bowling? A huge inswinger, on off, Babar Azam does really well to bring his bat down in time and jam it out.
Outside off, driven towards covers.
Back of a length, on off. Babar Azam covers the line and blocks.
Outside off, on a length, Babar Azam is happy to leave it alone.
Touch fuller, on off, angling in. Babar Azam gets behind and blocks.
Abdullah Shafique clips this loopy ball to deep square leg for a couple.
On middle, kept out.
Tossed up, on middle. Abdullah Shafique stays solid in defence.
On the pads, glanced behind square on the leg side for a single.
Very full, on off. Babar Azam defends.

Loopy ball, outside off. Babar Azam presses forward to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to the off side. No harm done. The Pakistan dressing room are on their feet to appreciate this partnership. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 4!
This is pitched up, around off and there's bit of an away shape on it. Shafique leaves it alone.
A length ball, in that channel around off and the ball just holds its line. Shafique makes a watchful leave.
On a good length over off stump. Shafique gets right behind the line of the ball to block.
This one zipped through! Full and outside off. Shafique makes another leave and Alex Carey collects the ball around head height.
WIDE! Full and very wide, beyond the tramline.
Pitched up, around off and Shafique lets it through to the keeper.
On leg stump, Shafique dabs it back onto the deck off the back foot.
Angled into middle at around 140 clicks. Babar Azam blocks it out solidly.
Fullish delivery, around off. This is driven straight towards extra cover.
Cummins tries to skid one through at 143 clicks but Azam does well to defend it out.
Babar Azam gets his first runs of the day. On off, dabbed down towards point for a quick single.
A length ball, sliding into middle and leg. Shafique keeps it out.
Another pacy delivery, full and attacking the stumps. Shafique stays solid in defense.
Good-length ball, over leg stump. Azam plays it with soft hands towards short cover and sets off for a single. Good running.
Close to the off stump, zipping through to the keeper as Shafique makes another leave.
Length, at 142 clicks and around the hips. Shafique defends it towards mid-wicket.
A bumper now, over middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique sways his head away from the line of the ball.
Around the top of middle. Shafique blocks it out.
A touch fuller, around off. Shafique looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the blade and the ball goes nowhere.
Right on the money! Around off and just tailing in a bit. Babar Azam manages to keep it out.
Sliding into middle and leg, Azam works it well in front of square on the leg side and picks up a couple of runs.
Angling into middle at 145 clicks. Azam gets right behind the line of the ball to make the block.

A bit of uncertainty from Babar Azam. This is banged in short and outside off. Azam sets up to play the ramp shot but the ball doesn't bounce anywhere as much as it should. Azam ends up helping it to deep point for a single.
Angled into middle and leg. Blocked out.
Pitched up, on off. Shafique defends it out.
Flashy from Babar Azam and it could have been catastrophic! A cross-seamed delivery, angled across the right-hander. Azam hangs back and goes after it but gets beaten by the pace and bounce.
Around the off pole, left alone.

Peach! On a nagging length at almost 145 clicks, in that channel around off and the ball seems to go across but holds its line ever so slightly. Azam has a poke at it but gets beaten past the outside edge.
On off. Blocked.
Fuller in length, sliding across the off stump. Left alone by Babar Azam.
Length this time, angled across the right-hander. Azam watches the ball as he lets it through to the keeper.

Bonus runs and Abdullah Shafique has his first runs of the day. Angled into the body, Shafique dabs it down to mid-wicket for a quick run. David Warner has a pop at the bowler's end but Shafique is well in. The ball hist the stumps and rolls towards the fence as there's no one backing up. The batters get a couple of additional runs. The 200 is up for Pakistan.
Drop and run! On off, bunted away on the off side for another quick single.
Back of a length, around off. Shafique taps it towards cover-point for one more.
On off and nipping back in. Azam plays a solid defensive shot.
This is sliding down the leg side, Azam looks to flick but misses.
Half an appeal but there might have been bat involved. Full and angling into the pads. Azam gets an inside edge onto the pads and the ball rolls towards square leg. They sneak in a run as well.
FOUR! Swepson starts off with a friendly full toss and Babar Azam takes full advantage of it. On middle and leg, this is heaved through the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary by Azam.
FOUR! Another loosener from Mitchell Swepson and another boundary for Babar Azam. A half volley on the pads and this is flicked through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Much better from Swepson. Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Azam defends it out.
Quicker this time, around off. Azam makes the block.
Quicker again, around off. Azam rocks back and cuts it towards the cover region.

Her comes the wrong 'un! This is bowled around off and the ball doesn't spin in but just holds its line. Babar Azam pads it away and Swepson is interested. Pat Cummins has a chat with him and they decide not to take the review. The replays show that the impact was outside off and the ball was comfortably missing off stump.
Pitched up, on off and sliding in. Shafique stays solid in defense.
Well kept down! Banged in short and around off. Abdullah Shafique goes on the back foot and dabs it down past the slip cordon and towards third man. The batters come back for the second with ease.
Around the top of off, blocked out.
Fullish delivery, around off. Shafique defends it to short cover.
A well-directed bouncer over middle stump. Abdullah Shafique ducks under it and it is called a wide.
On off, blocked out.
Pitched up, on off. This is pushed towards mid off.
A full toss, on off and dipping on the batter. Azam heaves it straight towards mid on.
Shorter and around leg stump. Azam works it off the back foot 'round the corner for a single.
Slightly flighted, on middle. Shafique strides out to defend.
Swepson hasn't quite got his control right so far this morning. Loopy full toss, on off. Shafique flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Another full toss, on middle and Azam clips it to the left of deep mid-wicket for one more.
Flatter, pushed through on off and sliding on. Shafique goes back and across to defend.
Not that short, around middle and this one climbs on the batter. Babar Azam fends it off really well.
Fuller delivery, on off. Azam stays solid in defense.
Ooh, that one nipped back a bit. Fullish delivery, around off and nipping back in. Babar Azam tries to play it away from the body and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Brilliant effort from Marnus Labuschagne but the batter is well in. Around off, nudged towards cover-point for a quick single by Babar Azam.
NO BALL! Sliding into middle and leg, pushed towards mid on. Cameron Green has overstepped and a no ball is called.
A bouncer now, over middle and leg. Shafique ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Shafique hangs back and squeezes it through covers for a single. The 200 partnership is up between these two and what a stand it has been!
On a shorter length, drifted into leg and turning away. Shafique has enough time to keep it out on the off side.
A little bit of drift now for Swepson. Around middle and leg, Shafique keeps it out.
A low full toss on the pads, Shafique flicks it past short leg for a single.
Fuller, on off and turning away. Babar Azam works it towards covers.
Quicker this time, fired into middle. Azam flicks it down to deep mid-wicket for one more.
A bit of flight, drifted into middle and turning away a bit. Shafique makes a watchful leave.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Azam presses forward to defend.
Outside off again, Azam strides out to negate the turn and defends it out.
Flatter this time, pushed through on off. Azam keeps it out off the back foot.
A touch quicker, on off and turning into the batter. Azam keeps it down towards short leg.
On off. Blocked out.
Flighted and on off. Babar Azam leans forward to make the block. Maiden!
Mitchell Swepson lets out a loud grunt as he delivers another full toss on the pads. Shafique heaves it down to deep mid-wicket and turns the strike over.
This one slides onto the pads. Azam keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! Drifted onto middle and leg, turning away a bit. Azam makes a watchful leave.
On middle, Azam with a solid front foot defensive shot.
Quicker this time, full and attacking the stumps. Babar Azam manages to get his blade on it in time.
On middle and skidding through. Azam works it towards wide mid on.
On a length, around off. Shafique defends it out on the leg side.

Turning into middle, Shafique tucks it away to short leg. There's an appeal for a catch by Marnus Labuschagne but it's a bit of a friendly one. The umpires though just want to make sure and go upstairs. The soft signal is not out and the replay shows that the ball cleared bounced and then went into the clutches of Marnus Labuschagne.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
On off again, blocked out.
On middle, turned to mid-wicket by Shafique.
Fuller in length, sliding onto the pads. Abdullah Shafique flicks it straight to backward square leg.
Nicely tossed up on middle. This one turns away a bit but Azam stays watchful in defense.
Flatter this time, on off. This is pushed off the back foot towards short cover.
Around off and there's a bit of drift in this time. Azam keeps it out.
Around middle and leg, Azam plays it with soft hands and keeps it down on the leg side.
This is pushed through on off. Azam keeps it out.
Nicely bowled and it's a maiden from Mitchell Swepson. Flighted, around off and Azam defends it off the front foot.
Quicker delivery on off. Shafique keeps it out.
Outside off this time and a bit quicker again. Shafique reaches forward and blocks it out.
Outside off, hitting the rough once again. Shafique leans forward and gets it off the inner half of the bat towards square leg.
Lyon just keeps hitting the rough and that is good accuracy from him. Shafique puts a big stride forward to defend.
On off. Blocked out.
Flatter this time, on off. Shafique stays back and works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On middle. Blocked out.
Flatter this time, around off. Shafique stays watchful in defense.
On middle and leg and it is the wrong 'un. Shafique goes deep in his crease and flicks it towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Fuller this time, on leg stump. This is worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A low full toss, this is pushed back to the bowler.
On middle. Blocked out.
On a length, around off. Shafique defeends it out.
Full and outside off. Shafique looks to cover drive but gets it off the inside edge towards short fine leg.
Full, arlound off. Blocked out.
Flatter this time, close to the off pole. Shafique taps it onto the off side.
And again! Around off. Blocked out.
Nicely flighted, on off. This one turns in and bounces a bit extra. Shafique gets hit on the thigh pad as he looks to work it leg side.
Tossed up, around middle. Azam keeps it out.
FOUR! Skillful from Babar Azam. This is on the pads, Azam gets inside the line of the ball and paddles it into the fine leg fence.
On middle. Blocked out.
Full again, at the toes. Azam works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slowed up, on middle. Shafique leans forward to defend.
A tad short and wide, Abdullah Shafique rocks back and cuts it behind point for just a single.
Quicker, around 93 clicks and around off. Shafique punches it towards silly point.
This one keeps low! Flatter and around off. Abdullah Shafique does well to adjust to the bounce and cuts it past point for a single.

Ooh, that's a risky shot! Tossed up, well outside off and the ball lands on the rough. Babar Azam looks to thrash it through covers but the ball turns in a mile and keeps very low. The ball misses the off stump though.
Around off, defended out.

Nathan Lyon getting some turn and bounce now. On a length, on off and this one turns in sharply. Azam looks to defend off the front foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads and the ball lands just in front of short leg.
Flatter, on off. Azam gets behind the line of the ball to defend.
Babar Azam looking a bit edgy out there. Around off, nudged onto the off side by Shafique and Azam wants the single. He is sent back in time by his partner.
FOUR! Exquisite from Abdullah Shafique and he moves into the 90s now. Tossed up, on off. Shafique dances down the track and creams it through extra cover for a boundary.
On off, pushed back towards the bowler.
Around off, a bit of drift in. Shafique blocks it out.
Flatter this time, on off. Shafique hangs back and defends it out.
Another one that keeps low! Flatter and close to the off pole. Shafique makes a watchful leave.
On a length, turning in from outside off. Babar Azam presses forward and defends it to silly point.
On middle, kept out by Azam.
Quicker and shorter, lands on a rough outside off and turns back in sharply. Azam rocks back and plays it on the leg side.
Well bowled and well played. Flatter, around off and the ball turns back in sharply again. Azam just about manages to get a bat on it.
Fuller, around off. Azam defends it off the front foot.
Flatter again, on off. Babar Azam blocks it out. Maiden!
Floats it up, on the pads. Shafique works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full toss, on middle. Babar Azam steps out and heaves it past wide mid on for a couple of runs.
On middle. Blocked out.
On middle, a little bit of drift in. Azam presses forward to defend.
Shorter and on middle. Azam works it off the back foot through mid-wicket for a run.
Flatter, around off and turning away. Shafique cuts it towards point.
Quicker one, full and outside off. Babar Azam strides out to defend but gets an outside edge which lands just in front of first slip.
Around off, pushed out on the off side.
Attacking middle and leg this time, worked towards mid-wicket.
On a length, on off and turning in. Azam looks to flick it away but decides to block in the end and the ball hits high on the bat.
Flatter delivery, on off. Kept out by Azam.
Around off, pushed out on the off side.
A bit slower and sliding down the leg side. Good take from Carey behind the stumps.
Length ball, around off. Shafique taps it to short cover.
A bit wider this time. Shafique stands tall and mistimes his drive towards mid off.
Around the top of off. Shafique dabs it down on the off side and looks for the single but Babar Azam sends him back.
Pitched up, on off. This is punched towards mid off.
FOUR! Cut-away and cut-away well by Abdullah Shafique. Short and wide, Shafique hangs back and thrashes it into the vacant backward point fence.
On a length, on the sixth stump line. Azam gets behind the line to make the block.
On off. Blocked out.
A bit shorter, on off. Azam wrists it off the back foot to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted, around off and turning in. Shafique leans forward to defend but gets undone in flight and gets hit on the body.
On off. Kept out.
This is pushed through on middle. Shafique stays solid in defense.
Full and sliding into off stump at 140 clicks. Babar punches it firmly back towards the bowler.
Pitched up on off. Azam defends it out.
Cummins goes wider of the crease and slants it into middle and leg. Azam pushes it towards mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. Babar Azam slashes it to deep backward point for a single.
Shafique wants the single but is sent back and rightly so. On off, nudged onto the off side.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Pat Cummins goes wide of the crease again and angles it on a nagging length, from outside off. Abdullah Shafique is enticed into playing the cover dfrive but it just isn't full enough to drive. Shafique ends up playing a bit away from the body and gets a thick outside edge towards first slip. Steven Smith over there takes a sharp catch and Australia have the breakthrough they so desperately needed and it's the skipper who has stepped up. Heartbreak for Shafique though as he departs for 96 well made runs.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Full and angled onto the pads from 'round the stumps. Azam clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Around off and tailing back in sharply. Fawad Alam gets an inside edge through square leg and sets off for a single. He survives the King Pair.

Big mix-up in the middle but Fawad Alam survives. On off, tapped towards short cover for a quick single. Babar Azam wants it but Alam hesitates a bit and has to put in the desperate dive. Marnus Labuschagne misses the direct hit at the keeper's end and Alam is a relieved man.
Full and around off, driven towards covers.
A hint of reverse there from Mitchell Starc and Fawad Alam plays it well. Full, tailing into middle. Alam with an on drive, through mid on and picks up a couple of runs.
Full and on off. Alam bunts it back to the bowler and that will be Lunch on Day 5!
Fuller in length, on off. Babar Azam plays it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Babar Azam punches it off the back foot to deep backward point for a single.
Comes 'round the wicket for the left-hander, a length ball, on middle. Fawad Alam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off, Fawad Alam lets that one through.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Fawad Alam shuffles across and has an unconvincing wristy prod at it. Luckily for him, it just fizzes past the edge!
Touch fuller, outside off. Fawad Alam leaves it alone.
Spears a length ball, outside off, angling in. Babar Azam has a poke but gets beaten as the ball keeps low.
Length ball, on off. Babar Azam works it to mid-wicket for one.

Back of a length, outside off. Fawad Alam slaps it through covers and gets three runs. Maybe Mitchell Starc should try to bowl full and get Alam hit on the pads as he has a very unusal batting stance. Just like he did in the first innings.
Short of a length, on off. Babar Azam knocks it to point for a run.
Here comes the full ball! A yorker, on middle and leg. Fawad Alam picks it up and digs it out on the leg side.
Fuller, outside off. Fawad Alam squeezes it out.
An inswinger, on off. Babar Azam mistimes his drive to mid off.
An inswinging yorker, on off. Azam plays it back to the bowler.

On a good length, on middle, Babar Azam stands tall and looks to defend but gets beaten due to the lack of bounce. Pat Cummins appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no. Australia don't opt for the review. Replay shows that there was an inside edge on that one.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Babar Azam clips it to square leg for a run.
Length ball, on off, keeps a touch low. Fawad Alam manages to defend it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, outside off. Alam leaves it untouched.
Length ball, on off. Babar Azam with a solid front foot defence.
Angling in a length ball, on off. Babar Azam tries to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to the second slip fielder. Didn't carry as it was played with soft hands.
FOUR! Lovely! Length ball, outside off. Babar Azam leans and plays a beautiful cover-drive. Elegance at it's best and the ball races away to the fence. He moves into 140s now!
This keeps low! Length ball, on the pads. Azam nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
A bumper, on middle. Fawad Alam sits under it.
Full and shaping into middle and leg, Fawad clips it on the up and it drops just short of the fielder stationed in the short mid-wicket region. An inspired field placement that!
Short delivery, on middle, beautifully directed. Babar Azam hops and blocks it out.
Follows it with a full ball, on middle, tailing back in. Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off. Azam drives it to mid off.
Fuller in length, outside off. Babar Azam squeezes it out to square of the wicket and into the deep for a brace.
Full and shaping in, on off. Babar Azam plays it down to deep backward point for a single.
Full and well outside off, Fawad Alam lets it be.
A wide yorker, outside off, at 140.2 kph. Babar Azam squeezes it out to backward point for a single.
Length ball, tailing back in, on off. Alam keeps it out to square leg.
On the pads and Alam clips it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Full and outside off, Alam pats it back to the bowler.
A full toss, on off, coming in. Fawad Alam covers the line and knocks it in front of mid on.
Back of a length, on middle. Fawad Alam hops back in his crease and keeps it out.
Back of a length, on off. Azam stands tall and blocks it right under his eyes.
Length ball, on off. Babar Azam blocks.
An outswinging yorker this time, on off. Babar Azam jams it out.
Length ball drifting on the pads, Babar Azam works it to deep square leg for a run.
Hits the deck on a length and Fawad Alam does well to knock this to cover-point.
On off, nipping away. Fawad Alam gets behind and taps it to point.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam hangs back and defends.
Full and on off, blocked.
Tossed up, on middle, Babar Azam presses forward and keeps it out.
Short and on off, punched off the back foot through covers for a brace. He moves to 149!

Babar Azam has stepped up truly and is still looking for more! He gets his150! What an incredible knock this has been from him. Loopy ball, on middle. Azam turns it on the leg side for a single. He gets a huge cheer from the crowd. His partner walks up to him and gives him a handshake.
Outside off, Alam puches it to wide of mid off for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Fawad Alam lets it through.
Touch fuller, on off. Alam brings his bat down and defends.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Cometh the hour, cometh the man! Perfect line, perfect length from the Australian skipper and he gets his reward once again! If Babar Azam is leading from the front for Pakistan, Pat Cummins is not hanging back. He gets the breakthrough once again. Good-length ball, angled into off and just holding its line. Fawad Alam has a poke at it and this time the ball kisses the outside edge. Alex Carey behind the stumps makes no mistake and the Aussie players are pumped up.
Howout: c Alex Carey b Pat Cummins

Commentary: Full, on middle and leg. Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out.
Mohammad Rizwan nudges this length ball on the leg side.
Full and shaping in, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan defends it with soft hands towards cover-point as it keeps low. What an over from the skipper!
Tossed up, on off. Azam prods and blocks.
Attacking line, outside off. Babar Azam lunges and defends it out.
Turning in, outside off, Babar Azam looks to defend but gets hit near the box.
Outside off, pushed towards covers off the back foot.
Floats it up, on off. Azam is solid in his defence.
Full and outside off, blocked. A maiden!
Length ball, on middle. Rizwan covers the line and tucks it to mid-wicket.

Short of a length, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan hops onto his toes and scythes it through covers. The ball dies in front of the ropes before the fielder collects it on the chase and Rizwan gets underway with three!
Short ball, on middle. Azam waits for it and pulls it at the last moment to deep square leg for a single.
Again! Length ball, wide outside off. Mohammad Rizwan punches it through covers. Gets three again!
Full and tailing back in, on off. Azam digs it out.
Short of a length, on off. Azam rides the bounce and punches it towards covers. Marnus Labuschagne there does well to stop the ball.
Full and outside off, pushed to mid off.
Outside off, kept out.
A low full toss, outside off, Mohammad Rizwan drives it to mid on and crosses ends.
Floats it up, on off. Nudged to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, blocked out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Babar Azam keeps it out.
Green keeps it full and straight to Rizwan, who pushes it out to mid on.
Well bowled from Cameron Green. Slanted into middle and this one tailed in. Mohammad Rizwan is a bit late on it but gets enough bat on it to keep it out.
Very full this time, close to the off pole. Rizwan jams it out on the off side.
On a good length, over off. Rizwan hops and keeps it down to short mid-wicket.
Green pushes this one fuller and wider, with the ball tailing in a bit. Mohammad Rizwan goes chasing after it but the ball sneaks past the bottom edge.
Length, around off and coming back into the right-hander. Rizwan nudges it out on the leg side.
Nicely flighted, outside off. Azam presses forward and pushes it to silly point.
Around off and turning in. Azam goes deep in his crease and turns it through square leg for a single.
Looped up, on off and turning in. Rizwan blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off. Rizwan thrashes it past a leaping fielder at silly point for a run.
Sliding onto the pads, flicked away leg side.
Ooh, that one kept low! Drifted into the pads, Azam looks to push it onto the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Around the top of off. Blocked out.
Just a bit of feistiness shown here by Cameron Green. Pitched up on off, Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler who tries to throw the ball back onto the stumps and catch Rizwan off guard.
This is banged in short, around off. Mohammad Rizwan pulls it away aerially towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Full and straight, sliding on. Azam pushes it to mid on.
NO BALL! On off, Azam stays solid in defense. Green has overstepped and a no ball is called.
Length this time, on off stump. Azam bunts it out on the off side.
Full and a bit wider, on that sixth stump line. Babar Azam shoulders arms.
A touch fuller and flatter, on off. Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
Around off, Rizwan strides out to block.
Slightly flighted, around off again. Rizwan presses forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Around middle this time, Rizwan keeps blocking it away.
Quicker delivery, darted into middle. Rizwan defends it out with a straight bat.
Nicely flighted, on off. Rizwan blocks it out once again. Maiden!
Full, on middle and just turning away a bit. Azam nudges it out on the off side.
Flatter this time, on middle. Azam hangs back and keeps it out.
Drifted in fuller and at 89 clicks. Azam works it towards mid-wicket.
Nicely flighted, around off. Babar Azam strokes it through extra cover for a single.

Peach! Mitchell Swepson puts a lot more revs on the ball and gets it to drift towards leg stump. The ball pitches and turns away sharply as Mohammad Rizwan is unable to get a stride forward. The ball goes off the outside edge and lands a bit short and wide of Steven Smith at first slip.
Beaten! On off, this one grips and turns sharply. Rizwan tries to defend with a straight bat but is comprehensively beaten.
On off and turning in. Azam nudges it on the leg side.
Quicker one, around off. Azam blocks it out.

FOUR! Babar Azam gets a bit aggressive and takes Nathan Lyon on. Tossed up, around off. Azam skips down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball before lifting it well over wide mid on for a boundary.

NOT OUT! Close but not close enough for Nathan Lyon and Australia. This is flighted around off and Babar Azam puts a big stride forward looking to defend. The ball turns in and Azam misses. He gets rapped on the pads and Lyon seems certain. Aleem Dar shakes his head and Pat Cummins has reviewed it. UltraEdge confirms that there's no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that the impact is in line but the ball is just clipping the leg stump. Azam survives on umpire's call.
Around off. Blocked.

Flatter delivery, this is spilled down the leg side. Babar Azam shuffles a bit and tickles it really fine. David Warner chases it down from short fine leg and puts in the dive to stop the boundary. Three taken.
On middle. Blocked out.
A touch shorter, on middle and leg. Azam goes deep in his crease to work it through mid-wicket for a single.
Nice drift again, on the pads. Rizwan nudges it through square leg for a run.
Flatter delivery, close to the off pole. Azam punches it out to cover-point.
On middle, solidly defended off the front foot by Azam.
Here comes the wrong 'un. This is on off and turning in. Babar Azam picks it out early and makes the block.
A bit quicker and fuller, around off. Rizwan strides out to defend.
And again! Around off, Rizwan presses forward to defend.
Flatter this time, turning into off. Mohammad Rizwan goes on the back foot to keep this one out.
Darted into off. Rizwan makes another solid block.
Nicely bowled! Lyon slows it up and bowls it on off. The ball turns in a bit more and stays low as well. Rizwan does well to keep it out.
Turning into the pads, this is flicked towards square leg.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Azam punches it firmly towards mid off.
On off. Defended off the front foot.
This is bowled a touch quicker and attacking the pads. Azam fends it away.

Dropped! This could be a huge moment in the match. Tossed up, on off. Babar Azam pushes at it but hits it uppishly to the right of Travis Head at silly point. He sticks out a right hand but is unable to hold on. Sharp chance but Head should have grabbed it.

Another chance, now on the other side. Fuller, on middle and Azam nudges it the right of short leg where the fielder once again sticks out a right hand but this is a lot more difficult than the previous one. Babar Azam hanging on the edge here.
On off, pushed wide of silly point.
Flighted, full and around off. Blocked out.
Lyon pulls back the length and bowls it on off. Rizwan defends it off the back foot.
A bit wider of off stump now and Rizwan puts a stride forward to defend.
On middle, eased down to mid on.
Flighted, on a length and turning in. Mohammad Rizwan goes back and across to flick it leg side.
Close to the off stump. Blocked.

FOUR! After a couple of close shaves in the previous Swrpson over, Babar Azam decides to take him on. Tossed up, on off. Azam steps down the track and drives it straight back past the bowler for a glorious boundary. The 300 is now up for Pakistan.
A bit shorter, around middle and leg. This is worked through mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! Australia get close once again but yet again it's umpire's call only. Mitchell Swepson sees Mohammad Rizwan advancing and tries to skid one through. The ball lands on middle and goes on with the angle. Rizwan pads it away and there is a huge appeal from the visitors. The umpire remains unmoved and it is reviewed. UltraEdge shows there's no spike and Ball Tracker shows the wickets are hitting but the impact is umpire's call (more than 3 meters down the track) and Rizwan lives on.
On middle. Blocked.
Fuller this time, around off. Rizwan drives it gently past silly point.
On off, pushed back towards the bowler.
Fullish ball, outside off. Babar Azam hangs back and pushes it out towards cover-point for an easy single.
This is angled into the off stump. Rizwan keeps it out.
Length this time, slanting in from outside off. Rizwan stays on his toes and makes the block.
Good-length ball over off. This is bowled at 140.5 clicks and Rizwan gets right behind the line to make the block.

FOUR! Starc looks for the dream delivery, angled into the pads looking to bring it away but ends up serving a half-volley. Mohammad Rizwan flicks it through mid-wicket and picks up a boundary. Less than 200 required now for Pakistan to win.
Fuller in length, on off. Kept out.
Ripper of a delivery from Swepson! Tossed up, on a nagging length and on off. The ball grips and turns away sharply. Azam gets pushed onto the back foot and gets beaten past the outside edge.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Babar Azam hops onto the back foot and punches it through covers for a single.
On middle and leg, worked away leg side.
Nicely slowed up again, on middle. Rizwan pushes it towards mid on.
A bit quicker again, on off and asking the batter to drive. Rizwan does so but along the ground.
Beaten! Quicker one, at 93 clicks and this is pushed through close to the off stump. Mohammad Rizwan rocks back to cut but the ball zips past the outside edge.
On middle. Blocked out.

Just short! This is flighted on a length and around middle and leg. The ball bounces a bit and as Azam looks to tuck it 'round the corner but gets an inside edge onto the pads and ball falls short of silly mid on.
On middle. Kept out.
Just short again! This is pushed through on middle. Babar Azam just plays a gentle defensive shot but Marnus Labuschagne is really close in at short leg and the ball lands just in front of him.
