On a length, around off. Azam keeps it out on the off side.
This is a bit shorter and spinning down leg. Babar Azam just dabs it down past short leg and that will be Tea on Day 5!
Floats it up, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out.
Tossed up, spinning away from middle. Mohammad Rizwan manages to block it out.
Full and on off, Mohammad Rizwan presses forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Drags it short and on middle, Mohammad Rizwan is not going to miss out on those. He hangs back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! A full toss, on off, Mohammad Rizwan picks it early and smashes it to deep mid-wicket again to collect another boundary.
On the pads this time, Mohammad Rizwan clips it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs. Good start for Pakistan post-Tea.
Flatter, on off. Azam is watchful in his defence.
SIX! Takes the aerial route now! Are Pakistan going for a win? Loopy ball, outside off, Babar Azam shimmies down the track and tonks it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Outside off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks.
Drifiting in, on middle. Babar Azam blocks it out off the back foot.
Extra bounce! Tossed up, on middle, Babar Azam tucks it on the leg side. Came off the gloves.

FOUR! More runs! Floats it up, on leg, Babar Azam rocks back and glances it with soft hands to fine leg for a boundary. 20 runs have come in the last two overs. Pakistan have up the ante after Tea interval.
Slower through the air, outside off, keeps low. Mohammad Rizwan pushes it to the off side.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Shortish, on off. Punched towards covers.
Tossed up, outside off. Rizwan pushes it to point.
Full and on off, Mohammad Rizwan prods and drives it towards covers.
That keeps low! Flatter, on middle, keeps really low. Mohammad Rizwan stays back and smacks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, played straight to mid on.
Floats it up, on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Full again, outside off. Blocked out.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Rizwan rocks back and defends.
On middle, kept out.
Flighted delivery, on off. Mohammad Rizwan works it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Drifted on the pads, this is clipped away through square leg for a single.
On middle and leg, Azam strides out and nudges it past short leg for one more.
Nicely bowled! Fuller, close to the off pole and turning away. Rizwan makes a watchful leave.
Two is the call and they get it with ease. Slightly shorter on middle. Mohammad Rizwan works it off the back foot through mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed up, well outside off. Rizwan drives it towards wide mid off.
Floated up, on off. Rizwan presses forward to defend.
Flatter delivery, outside off. Babar edges it down towards backward point with soft hands and picks up a single.
Around off. Blocked.
Flighted, around off and turning in. Rizwan hops back to defend.
Shorter and spinning into leg. Rizwan rocks back, makes a bit of room and works it to deep square leg for a run.
Ooh, a bit of bite there! Tossed up on a length and well outside off. The ball hits a rough patch and turns and bounces sharply. Babar is taken by surprise but manages to keep it down.
On off. Kept out by Babar.
FOUR! Crunched! Swepson comes 'round the wicket and sets up the field for the sweep shot. This is spilled down the leg side. Rizwan takes it on and paddles it with disdain into the fine leg fence.
Quicker one, on the pads. Rizwan dabs it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
WIDE! Tossed up, well outside the leg stump. Azam leaves it alone and a wide is called.
Shorter one, around leg. Azam goes on the back foot to work it through square leg for one.
What even was that? This is a full toss, down the leg side. Mohammad Rizwan this time gets his left pad onto the ball while falling over a bit.
Full, on off and driven towards the cover region.
This is down the leg side, Rizwan sweeps it behind square on the leg side and picks up a single.
Turning in from well outside off. Rizwan taps it to silly point.
Flatter this time, around off. This is cut away towards backward point.
And again! Around off, cut away towards point off the back foot.
On off, Rizwan defend sit off the front foot.
Shorter and outside off, turning in a long way. Rizwan works it to short leg.
This is flighted and pushed wider. Mohammad Rizwan goes chasing after it and gets a bottom edge down to short third man. Maiden over for Nathan Lyon.
Tossed up, on off. Azam caresses it along with the spin towards deep cover for a single.
Another full toss from Swepson, on leg stump. Mohammad Rizwan brooms it away past the fielder at short leg for a couple of runs.
On off. Blocked.
Flatter, on off. Rizwan punches it off the back foot towards mid off.
Down the leg side and turning back into the batter. Rizwan looks to sweep it fine but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Slower through the air and flighted outside off. Babar Azam uses his feet and eases it down to long on for a run.
Tossed up well outside off. Mohammad Rizwan gets low and drags the sweep shot towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Around off, wristed through square leg for one more.
Slowed up a bit, on off. Babar defends it out.

FOUR! It is there to hit and Babar Azam doesn't miss out. Floated up, outside off. Azam stands tall and crunches it through extra cover for a glorious boundary. Less than 150 required now to win. This is now the highest ever score by a Test captain in the fourth innings of a Test match.
Close to the off pole, Azam blocks it out.
Down the leg side, swept away to fine leg for a single.
Down the leg side again, fuller and Azam pads it away.
Full again, around leg stump. Azam gets his pads in the way.
On leg stump, Azam works it towards square leg.
Turning into the batter from outside leg and Azam looks to pad it away. He misses but gets hit on the back leg.
On off, pushed away onto the off side.
Shorter and on the body. Rizwan shuffles across and looks to pull but gloves it away to fine leg for a single.
Pitched up on middle. Azam presents a dead bat at it.
Full again, trying to skid one through on off. Azam hangs back and drives it towards mid on.
This is banged in halfway down the track and down the leg side. Azam leaves it alone and Carey does well to dive forward as the ball dies on him.
Around off, Azam plays away from the body and steers it to deep point for a run.
Fullish ball, outside off. Rizwan hangs back and kee[ps it out on the off side.
Flighted, around off. Babar Azam defends it out with soft hands.
T7urning in from outside off and there's a bit of an extra bounce. Azam hops back and keeps it down to short leg.
On middle, worked away on the leg side.
Edged but safe! Outside off and this one turn, Azam looks to play for the turn but the ball catches the outside edge and lands well in front of Smith at first slip.
On off and turning in. Blocked out.
Slowed up, around off. Azam pushes it out towards covers.
Fullish ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan is pushed back on the back foot and edges it down towards third man for a couple of runs.
Straight into the body of Travis Head at short leg. On middle, Rizwan flicks it straight to short leg.
FOUR! Short ball, down the leg side. Rizwan gets in position quickly and pulls it hard and low into the backward square leg fence. He moves on to 49 now.
Full and wide, Rizwan defends it out.
Banged in short on middle. Mohammad Rizwan pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple more and that brings up his fifty. Brilliant knock so far and can he now do the unthinkable?
Back of a length, on off. Rizwan punches it off the back foot through covers for a run.
Floats it up, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan goes for the sweep but gets struck on the pads.
Full and on off, Mohammad Rizwan steps out and yorks himself. Nudges it to mid-wicket.
Spinning in from outside off, Mohammad Rizwan plays it to long on for a run.
Full and outside off, eased down to long on for one.
Full again, outside off. Rizwan drills it down the ground to long on and crosses ends.
Tossed up, on off. Azam with a solid front foot defence.
Pitching it outside leg, Mohammad Rizwan is so good with the sweep shot. Sweeps it well to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy, on middle. Azam keeps it out with a dead bat.
Shortish, on off. Azam works it to wide of mid-wicket for a run.
Little bit short, outside off. Rizwan smacks it to mid off.
Flighted delivery, full, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan comfortably sweeps it to deep square leg. He rotates the strike.
Full and on off, kept out. 20 overs left and Pakistan need 131 runs. Will Pakistan pull a trigger and turn on the T20 mode?
Loopy ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan lunges forward and knocks it towards covers for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Babar Azam gets behind the line and blocks.
Slower through the air, on off. Blocked out.
Floats it up, on off, extra bounce on that one. Azam stays solid in defence.
Full and on off, kept out.
Full and on off, blocked.
Quicker and sliding on, Mohammad Rizwan knocks it towards covers for a single. 100-run stand comes up between these two!
Flatter, on middle. Blocked.
On the pads, worked to mid on for a run.
Floats it up, on leg. Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out.
A googly, on middle. Worked to deep mid-wicket for one.
Very full, on off. Babar Azam jams it out back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan eases it to long on for a run.
Shorter, outside off. Azam knocks it in front of cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Babar Azam is very solid in his defence.
Quicker, outside off, at 88.2 kph. Babar Azam meets it with a dead bat.
Floats it up, on middle. Babar Azam manages to bring his bat down in time as that kept really low.
Loopy ball, on off. Azam with a front foot defence.
Short ball, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan pulls it along the carper but the ball hits Travis Head at short leg.
A bouncer, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan ducks under it.
WIDE! Too short and down leg, Mohammad Rizwan does not bother to play at it. Wide called for height.
Another bumper, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan sits under it.
Another short delivery, on leg. Mohammad Rizwan ducks once again. Aleem Dar signals two for the over..
Short of a length, on off. Mohammad Rizwan chops it to deep backward point for a single.
Full and on off, Babar Azam digs it out from the crease.
Full and outside off, Mohammad Rizwan goes for the drive but miscues it. The ball hits the cue end of the bat.
On middle, Mohammad Rizwan makes room and punches it towards covers.

Loopy ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan gets behind the line and then shoulders arms. The ball hits his pads and flies over Steven Smith at first slip. The ball rolls to third man but the batters decide not to run.
Spinning in from outside off, Rizwan is right behind the line to defend.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan blocks.
Tossed up, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan smothers it back by lunging forward.
Short ball, on off. Babar Azam sways away from the line and lets it sail through.
Short again angling down leg, Babar Azam watches it closely and shoulders arms.
Short of a length, on middle. Babar Azam swivels and tucks it to short leg.
Short of a length, down leg, Azam lets that one through as well.

Green comes 'round the wicket now and bowls a length ball, on middle. Babar Azam stays back to defend. Gets an inside edge and the ball rolls to backward square leg. He starts running for a single but is sent back by Mohammad Rizwan. Babar Azam wouldn't want to get run out that too when he is so near to his double hundred.
Short and banged it into the track, that barely got up but Babar decides to duck under it, strays it down the leg side.
Flighted delivery, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan plays it to mid on.
Drifting on the pads, Rizwan clears his front leg and tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Outside off, Mohammad Rizwan plays it very late to short third man for a run.

FOUR! The crowd is chanting Babar, Babar and he hits a boundary! Short from Swepson, on off. Babar Azam rocks back and smashes it through covers. Hits it in the gap and the ball races away to the fence. He moves to 195!
Another short ball, outside off. Babar Azam slaps it to sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan cuts it away to deep point and comes back for the second. Babar Azam will face the next over.
Tossed up, outside off. Babar Azam presses forward and blocks.
Short and outside off, Babar Azam cuts it to point.
Tossed up, outside off. Azam defends it to short leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Nathan Lyon gets the better of Babar Azam! A high-class innings comes to an end. Babar Azam walks off with just 4 runs short of his double ton. Would have been an elusive double hundred but wasn't to be. Heartbreak for him, heartbreak for the fans and the Karachi crowd is stunned. They are up on their feet and give him a huge applause which he deserves. Coming to the ball, it was a loopy delivery from Lyon, on off. Babar Azam pressed forward and tried to defend. Got an inside edge onto the pad and the ball lobbed in the air towards short leg where Marnus Labuschagne took it with both hands. Is that the opening Australia were looking for? Mind you that the new ball is around the corner.
Howout: c Marnus Labuschagne b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! What is happening out there? Is there a late twist in the tale? Nathan Lyon has been toiling away for about 50 odd overs and finally, he has his say in this Test match. Lyon drifts it into the pads, the ball turns away a bit after pitching. Faheem Ashraf looks to defend it with an angled bat and the ball goes off the outside edge towards first slip. Steven Smith takes a really good low catch and the visitors will now believe. Lyon is on a hat-trick and Sajid Khan is the new man in.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: No hat-trick for Nathan Lyon but he has done his job and Australian players are all re-energized now. Lyon drags the length short and Sajid hangs back to keep it out. The third new ball is now due. Will Cummins take it straightaway?
The third new ball is available and Australia waste no time to take it. Mitchell Starc steams in with the new ball and bowls an inswinging yorker, on middle. Mohammad Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan lifts his bat and lets it go.
Pitched up, on off. Rizwan defends it out.
Full and straight, searching for the inswinging yorker. Mohammad Rizwan does well to jam it out.
FOUR! Full again, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan leans in and thrashes it through covers for a glorious boundary.
Pitched up on middle and at 144.5 clicks. Rizwan pushes it firmly back towards the bowler who does well to get a hand on it. Dot to end and Rizwan fails to retain the strike.
On a length, around off and turning back in. Khan dabs it down to short leg.

Excellent shot but just for a single. Full and outside off, driven nicely through covers and the ball just doesn't have the legs to reach the ropes. It shouldn't have been an easy three but Sajid Khan pulled up a bit and they could get only one.
On off, Rizwan leans in to defend.
Drifted onto the pads, Rizwan goes on the back foot and keeps it out on the leg side.
Shorter this time, Rizwan pushes it through covers off the back foot and picks up a single.
Flighted this time, on middle. Sajid Khan stays solid in defense.
Good-length on off. Rizwan taps it back onto the deck.
FOUR! Wow! Pitched up, on of. Mohammad Rizwan with a beautiful cover drive through the infield and the ball races away to the fence.
Around off, this is blocked out towards covers.
Slanted into middle and leg, keeping a bit low. Rizwan defends it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! This is banged in short on off. Fast hands from Mohammad Rizwan as he gets right on top of the bounce and muscles it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Cummins bowls this one really short and wide. Rizwan goes chasing after it but misses.
Flatter, around off. Khan goes back and across and keeps it down towards point.
FOUR! Sajid Khan having a bit of fun out there. Tossed up on off, Khan goes down on one knee and slogs it away into the mid-wicket fence.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries and this game just keeps on getting more and more bizarre. On off, Khan with an uppish push past silly mid off and the timing is too good. The ball races away into the fence.
Fuller ball, close to the off stump. Khan blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off. Khan pushes it away onto the off side.

OUT! TAKEN! Steven Smith with another catch at first slip and Nathan Lyon has his fourth wicket! This match has just got way too interesting in the last few minutes and it's the visitors who are firmly in control now. Lyon pushes it through quicker and around off. Sajid Khan gets caught on the crease and goes on the back foot. Khan pushes at it with hard hands and with an angled bat. The ball goes off the outside edge and Smith takes another sharp catch. Australia need 3 wickets to win now with 8 overs still remaining in the day.
Howout: c Steven Smith b Nathan Lyon

Commentary: Tossed up, full and on middle. Rizwan jams it back towards the bowler.
The call is for two and they get it with ease. On off and skidding through. Rizwan rocks back and works it through extra cover, into the deep for a brace.
Slower through the air, drifted onto the pads. Rizwan defends it out.
Swepson goes quicker and fuller. Rizwan manages to keep it out.
Ooh, a bit of turn and that could have been it! Around off, the ball just stops in the pitch a bit and Mohammad Rizwan ends up getting a leading edge which falls safe around the cover region.
Full and on off, driven straight towards short cover and Rizwan cannot take the single to retain the strike.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Nauman Ali presses forward and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Ali keeps it out to the off side.
Quicker delivery at 94.5 kph. Nauman Ali blocks it out.
Floats it up, on middle. Ali keeps that one out.
Slower through the air, drifting on middle. Nauman Ali looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. Mild appeal for an lbw but not given.
Nauman Ali does well to defend this over. Presses forward to this last ball of the over and keeps it out.
SIX! That's a freebie! A full toss down leg, Mohammad Rizwan gets low and picks it up. He hammers it to deep square leg. Goes off the top edge but still goes the distance. He moves to 87!
Tossed up, on off. Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out. Defends it back to the bowler.
Sliding in on leg, Mohammad Rizwan tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and outside off, pushed to silly point.
Shortish, on middle and leg, keeps low as well. Mohammad Rizwan goes deep and whips it to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan chips it uppishly to mid off. Nauman Ali back on strike. 5 overs left and 3 wickets to win for Australia!
Drops it short, on off. Nauman Ali defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, turning away. Ali lunges forward and keeps it out.
Short and on off, Ali goes back and blocks.
Tossed up, on off. Ali presses forward and blocks it out. Nauman Ali is doing very well here.
Full and on off, defended out again.
Quicker delivery, on middle. Nauman Ali gets right behind the ball and defends it from the crease.
Short and sliding down leg, Mohammad Rizwan kicks it away with his pads.
Full and spraying down leg, Mohammad Rizwan goes for the hard sweep this time but misses.
A low full toss, on the pads. Mohammad Rizwan gets that away as he works it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Full and on leg, Mohammad Rizwan gets forward and clips it but the silly mid on fielder does well to stop it.
A full toss again, on the pads. Mohammad Rizwan kneels and sweeps it to deep square leg. It squirts past Lyon as the bal spins away and they scamper through for a brace.

DROPPED! Usman Khawaja what have you done? Loopy ball outside off, Rizwan reaches out for it and looks to drive but he chips it in the air to mid off and Khawaja doesn't get his hand underneath it but he spills that one in the end. Straight in and straight out but Usman Khawaja makes a meal out of it. What a twist that would have been had he grabbed it!

Marnus Labuschagne bowls it full and into the rough, outside off. Nauman Ali presses forward and look sto defend with an angled bat but misses. Appeal for caught behind but the umpire says no. Steven Smith at first sli[ is very excited as he thinks he heard something. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. Australia burn their review.
Floats it up, outside off. Ali keeps it out.

FOUR BYES! That took off from outside off, turning into Nauman who was getting behind to defend but misses, Alex Carey has no chance of stopping that and the ball runs all the way down to fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Nauman Ali puts a big stride forward and blocks.
A low full toss, outside off. Ali pushes it to mid off.
That's a brave leave! Into the rough, outside off. Nauman Ali shoulders arms.
Flatter ball, on off. Mohammad Rizwan defends.
FOUR! Mohammad Rizwan moves to 95! Lyon overcooks this one, on off. Mohammad Rizwan sees an opportunity and does not back away. He creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Short and on off, Mohammad Rizwan goes back and defends.

FOUR! Short and turning into Rizwan on the off stump, he goes on the backfoot and whips it with power, gets it past the silly mid on and short mid-wicket, runs all the way down to long-on for another boundary. Rizwan on 99 now!

Is Mohammad Rizwan safe? Yes, he is shows the replay. Mohammad Rizwan steps out and gets to the pitch of the ball. He pushes it back to Nathan Lyon who has a shy at the striker's end. However, Mohammad Rizwan makes it back with a desperate dive.

CENTURY! Mohammad Rizwan scores his second Test ton and becomes only the second Pakistan wicket-keeper to score a ton in the fourth innings! Take a bow! Steps out to this loopy ball and gets a leading edge towards covers but he scampers through to bring up his ton. He has played a match-saving innings here! Raises his hands, takes his helmet and acknowledges the applause from the crowd as well as his teammates,
Drifting down leg, Mohammad Rizwan sweeps but straight to leg slip.
Flighted on middle. Mohammad Rizwan keeps it out.
Flatter and on off, Mohammad Rizwan stays back and blocks it out.

FOUR! THAT'S IT! Players shake hands and walk off. Pakistan cling on to a draw. Credit to Australia for toiling so hard and not giving up. Kept everyone on toes till the very end. What a riveting last hour we had, it had everything but then no body deserved to lose and both the teams settle for a draw in the end. Coming to the ball, it was dropped short and kept low on the middle and leg, Mohammad Rizwan goes deep inside the crease and hoicks it to the vacant deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
